 part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":31,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Thomas Metham III was born about 1351, in Metham, Yorkshire, England, his father, Thomas Metham II, was 22 and his mother, Ann Tempest, was 18. He married Elizabeth Stapleton in 1362, in Cottam, Yorkshire East Riding, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died on 28 August 1403, in his hometown, at the age of 53."},"et":{"about 1351–28 August 1403":"umbes 1351–28. august 1403","1351–1403":"1351–1403","1348–1400":"1348–1400","1362–1391":"1362–1391","1370–Male":"1370–Surnud","1382–1416":"1382–1416","1331–1354":"1331–1354","1335–Female":"1335–Surnud","about 1382":"umbes 1382","1362":"1362","1351":"1351","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","4 August 1354":"4. august 1354","1391":"1391","Abt 1362":"umbes 1362","1349":"1349","1348":"1348","1403":"1403","1335":"1335","1400":"1400","28 August 1403":"28. august 1403","1354":"1354","1331":"1331","about 1351":"umbes 1351","1416":"1416","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Metham, Yorkshire, England":"Metham, Yorkshire, England","Howden, Yorkshire, England":"Howden, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1351–28 August 1403":"noin 1351–28. elokuuta 1403","1351–1403":"1351–1403","1348–1400":"1348–1400","1362–1391":"1362–1391","1370–Male":"1370–Kuollut","1382–1416":"1382–1416","1331–1354":"1331–1354","1335–Female":"1335–Kuollut","about 1382":"noin 1382","1362":"1362","1351":"1351","1382":"1382","1370":"1370"